<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-14716] Protocol frame checksumming options should not be case sensitive</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-14716</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Protocol v5 adds support for checksumming of native protocol frame bodies. The checksum type is negotiated per-connection via the &lt;tt&gt;STARTUP&lt;/tt&gt; message, with two types currently supported, Adler32 and CRC32. The mapping of the startup option value requested by the client to a &lt;tt&gt;ChecksumType&lt;/tt&gt; should not be case sensitive, but currently it is.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13184390">CASSANDRA-14716</key>
            <summary>Protocol frame checksumming options should not be case sensitive</summary>
