                            <comment id="16699533" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2018 20:20:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I might be missing it, and probably am, but what is the reason for not simply doing &lt;tt&gt;ChecksumType.valueOf(name.toUpperCase)&lt;/tt&gt;, and rethrowing &lt;tt&gt;IllegalArgumentException&lt;/tt&gt; as &lt;tt&gt;ProtocolException&lt;/tt&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;EDIT: Ok, I see, it&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;Adler32&lt;/tt&gt; not being low or upper case itself. Is it too late to change &lt;tt&gt;Adler32&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;ADLER32&lt;/tt&gt; at this point? Would it be desirable?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16699543" author="iamaleksey" created="Mon, 26 Nov 2018 20:30:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That said, +1 either way.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16699991" author="djoshi3" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2018 06:49:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Another option would be to use a static, immutable map of upper cased values to &lt;tt&gt;ChecksumType&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;and use that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16700148" author="beobal" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2018 09:58:12 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;Is it too late to change &lt;tt&gt;Adler32&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;ADLER32&lt;/tt&gt; at this point? Would it be desirable?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;No, I think that&apos;s acceptable and desirable, if only for consistency. This is the only usage of &lt;tt&gt;ChecksumType&lt;/tt&gt; where the algo is configurable, every other usage is hardcoded to &lt;tt&gt;CRC32&lt;/tt&gt;. We included support for &lt;tt&gt;Adler32&lt;/tt&gt; in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13304&quot; title=&quot;Add checksumming to the native protocol&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-13304&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-13304&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, rather than just removing that &lt;tt&gt;ChecksumType&lt;/tt&gt; to enable future potential perf improvements to be taken advantage of (&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13304?focusedCommentId=15923191&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15923191&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-13304?focusedCommentId=15923191&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-15923191&lt;/a&gt;). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Before committing I&apos;ll rename the enum value, re-run CI and post a message to dev list to be sure nobody objects to this post-freeze change. Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="16700372" author="beobal" created="Tue, 27 Nov 2018 12:51:23 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Rebased and updated branch to uppercase the enum value.&lt;/p&gt;
